Major News Items in leading S. African Newspapers
JOHANNESBURG , December 28 ( Xinhua ) -- The following are major news items in leading South African newspapers Monday :
The Citizen :
-- South African Deputy President Thabo Mbeki sent a strong warning Sunday to his countrymen against misuse of the country 's newly found democracy .
The Star :
-- Fire costed South Africa an unprecedented 1.2 billion Rand ( 200 million U.S. Dollars ) last year at an average rate of 3.3 million Rand ( 550,000 Dollars ) a day , the Fire Protection Association of South Africa announced Sunday .
Business Day :
-- Fear that South Africa has been importing millions of faulty condoms have prompted health professionals to call for an overhaul of the Health Department 's condom procurement procedures , health experts said Sunday .
Sowetan :
-- The death toll on South African roads since the start of the festive season beginning from December 1 stood at 555 Sunday , a spokesman for Arrive Alive Campaign said .
